<Base title="Terms of Service — ostk" description="Terms of service for ostk software and the ostk.ai website.">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="meta"><em>Effective: 2026-03-09</em> &middot; <a href="mailto:contact@ostk.ai">contact@ostk.ai</a></p>

    <h2>1. What this covers</h2>
    <p>These terms govern your use of ostk software and the ostk.ai website. ostk is open source software distributed under the MIT License.</p>

    <h2>2. The software</h2>
    <p>ostk is provided as-is. You can use, modify, and distribute it under the terms of the MIT License. The source code is available at <a href="https://github.com/os-tack">github.com/os-tack</a>.</p>

    <h2>3. No account required</h2>
    <p>ostk runs locally on your machine. There is no account creation, no authentication service, and no cloud dependency. You do not need to agree to these terms to use the software — the MIT License governs that. These terms cover the website and any hosted services (such as the needle-bench leaderboard).</p>

    <h2>4. needle-bench leaderboard</h2>
    <p>If you submit benchmark scores to the public leaderboard:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Scores are published with the model name and provider you specify</li>
      <li>You represent that scores are generated by running the standard bench suite without modification</li>
      <li>We reserve the right to remove scores that appear fabricated or generated from modified scenarios</li>
